he [[Figure skating at the 1988 Winter Olympics|1988 Winter Olympics]],<ref name=nyt880106/> as well as the [[1988 World Figure Skating Championships|1988 World Championships]]. Medals were awarded in four colors: gold (first), silver (second), bronze (third), and pewter (fourth) in four disciplines \u2013 [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]], and [[ice dancing]] \u2013 across three levels: senior, junior, and novice. The 1988 Championships took place between January 4 and 10, 1988 in [[Denver, Colorado]].\n\n==Senior-level results==\n\n===Men===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name\n! CF\n! SP\n! FS\n|- bgcolor=\"gold\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''1'''\n| [[Brian Boitano]] ||1||1||1\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''2'''\n| [[Paul Wylie]] ||3||3||2\n|- bgcolor=\"cc9966\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''3'''\n| [[Christopher Bowman]] ||2||2||\n|- bgcolor=\"#d1c571\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''4'''\n| [[Daniel Doran (figure skater)|Daniel Doran]] ||4||4||\n|-\n! 5\n| [[Angelo D'Agostino]]\n|-\n! 6\n| [[Scott Williams (figure skater)|Scott Williams]] ||5||||\n|-\n! 7\n| [[James Cygan]]\n|-\n! 8\n| [[Todd Eldredge]] ||9||||\n|-\n! 9\n| [[Doug Mattis]]\n|-\n! 10\n| [[Rudy Galindo]]\n|-\n! 11\n| [[Scott Kurttila]]\n|-\n! 12\n| [[Erik Larson (figure skater)|Erik Larson]]\n|-\n! 13\n| [[Mark Mitchell (American figure skater)|Mark Mitchell]]\n|-\n! 14\n| [[Craig Heath]]\n|-\n! 15\n| [[John Filbig]]\n|-\n! 16\n| [[Patrick Brault]]\n|-\n! 17\n| [[Brian Grant (figure skater)|Brian Grant]]\n|-\n! 18\n| [[Jon Robinson (figure skater)|Jon Robinson]]\n|-\n! 19\n| [[Tom Zakrajsek]]\n|-\n! 20\n| [[R. Todd Reynolds]]\n|}\n\n===Ladies===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name\n! CF\n! SP\n! FS\n|- bgcolor=\"gold\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''1'''\n| [[Debi Thomas]] ||1||1||1\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''2'''\n| [[Jill Trenary]] ||3||3||2\n|- bgcolor=\"cc9966\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''3'''\n| [[Caryn Kadavy]] ||2||2||3\n|- b