\u00e0 del Calcio AIC]] Career Award: 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/2018/12/totti-receives-career-award-at-gran-gala-del-calcio|title=TOTTI RECEIVES CAREER AWARD AT GRAN GALA DEL CALCIO|publisher=AS Roma|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Italian Football Hall of Fame]]: 2018<ref name=\"2018-SerieAHoF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.figc.it/it/formazione-ed-eventi/news/totti-zanetti-e-allegri-tra-i-premiati-dell-8-edizione-della-hall-of-fame-del-calcio-italiano/|title=Totti, Zanetti e Allegri tra i premiati dell\u20198\u00aa edizione della \u2018Hall of Fame del calcio italiano\u2019|publisher=FIGC.it|language=Italian|date=19 February 2019|accessdate=20 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Totti Champions Promenade Monaco.jpg|thumb|Totti's footprint on ''The Champions Promenade'' in [[Monaco]]]]\n\n'''Orders'''\n:[[File:Cavaliere OMRI BAR.svg|left|50px]] 5th Class / Knight: ''Cavaliere Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana'': 2000<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=79735|title=Cavaliere Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana|date=12 July 2000|accessdate=31 May 2011|publisher=Presidenza della Repubblica|language=Italian}}</ref>\n:[[File:Friedrich Order.png|left|50px]] [[Italian National Olympic Committee|CONI]]: Golden Collar of Sports Merit: ''Collare d'Oro al Merito Sportivo'': 2006<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.coni.it/it/news/primo-piano/49-primo-piano-2006/2935-coni-_consegna_dei_collari_d&rsquo%3Boro_e_dei_diplomi_d&rsquo%3Bonore-_premia_il_presidente_del_consiglio_romano_prodi-_diretta_tv_su_rai_2.html |title=Coni: Consegna dei Collari d\u2019Oro e dei Diplomi d\u2019Onore. Premia il Presidente del Consiglio Romano Prodi. Diretta Tv su Rai 2 |publisher=Comitato Olimpico Nazionale Italiano |work=Coni.it |language=Italian |date=16 October 2006 |accessdate=23 December 2016}}</ref>\n:[[File:ITA OMRI 2001 Uff BAR.svg|left|50px]] 4th Class / Official: ''Ufficiale Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana'': 2006<ref name=\"Presidenza della Repubblica\" />\n\n===Records===\n*Roma All-Time Leading Goalscorer: 307 goals\n*Roma All-Time Leading Goalscorer in Serie A: 250 goals\n*Roma All-Time Leading Goalscorer in UEFA Champions League: 17 goals\n*Roma All-Time Leading Goalscorer in UEFA Europa League: 21 goals\n*Roma All-Time Leading Goalscorer in UEFA Competitions: 38 goals\n*Roma All-Time Appearance Maker: 785 games\n*Roma All-Time Appearance Maker in Serie A: 618 games\n*Roma All-Time Appearance Maker in UEFA Champions League: 57 games\n*Roma All-Time Appearance Maker in UEFA Europa League: 46 games\n*Roma All-Time Appearance Maker in UEFA competitions: 103 games\n*[[European Cup and UEFA Champions League records and statistics#Oldest and youngest|UEFA Champions League]] oldest goalscorer: aged 38 years 59 days {{as of|2014|11|25|lc=y}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/picturegalleries/11132616/Francesco-Totti-tops-list-of-oldest-Champions-League-goalscorers.html|title=Francesco Totti tops list of oldest Champions League goalscorers|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=30 September 2014|accessdate=16 October 2015}}</ref>\n*Serie A youngest club's captain: aged 22 years 34 days<ref name=\"Totti: Serie A's youngest captain\"/>\n*Most goals for a single club in Serie A: 250 goals<ref name=\"Totti sets Serie A scoring record as Roma run riot\"/>\n*[[Football records in Italy#Goalscoring|Second-most goals scored in Serie A]]: 250 goals<ref name=\"Totti sets Serie A scoring record as Roma run riot\"/>\n*[[Derby della Capitale|Rome Derby]] All-Time Leading Goalscorer in Serie A: 11 goals<ref name=\"Roma vs. Lazio: 2-2\"/><ref name=\"Totti da record\"/>\n*[[Football records in Italy#Most goals from a penalty kick|Most penalties scored in Serie A]]: 71 goals<ref name=\"Did you know\"/><ref name=rigore/><ref name=\"La Juve si inceppa, Honda e Callejon da urlo\">{{cite news|url=http://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/fantacalcio/2014/10/20/news/la_juve_si_inceppa_honda_e_callejon_da_urlo-98532188/|title=La Juve si inceppa, Honda e Callejon da urlo|trans-title=Juve stalls, Fantastic Honda and Callejon|work=la Repubblica|language=Italian|date=20 October 2014|accessdate=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Serie A Week 34: Did You Know?\">{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/83190/serie-week-34-did-you-know|title=Serie A Week 34: Did You Know?|publisher=Football Italia|date=21 April 2015|accessdate=23 April 2016}}</ref>\n*Most different teams scored against in Serie A (alongside Roberto Baggio and Alberto Gilardino): 38<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/sport/gilardino-come-totti-e-baggio-gol-da-record-al-carpi_2157706-201602a.shtml|title=Gilardino come Totti e Baggio: gol da record al Carpi|publisher=Mediaset|language=Italian|date=30 January 2016|accessdate=6 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131210710/http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/sport/gilardino-come-totti-e-baggio-gol-da-record-al-carpi_2157706-201602a.shtml|archive-date=31 January 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*''Tutte le barzellette su Totti. (Raccolte da me)'', Milano, Mondadori, 2003. {{ISBN|88-04-52337-9}} (All the jokes about Totti. Collected by me) {{in lang|it}}\n*''Le nuove barzellette su Totti. (Raccolte ancora da me)'', Milano, Mondadori, 2004. {{ISBN|88-04-52482-0}} (The new jokes about Totti. Collected by me again) {{in lang|it}}\n*''\u00abMo je faccio er cucchiaio\u00bb. Il mio calcio'', Milano, Mondadori, 2006. {{ISBN|88-04-55733-8}} (I'm gonna chip him now. My football) {{in lang|it}}\n*''Tutto Totti, Milano, Mondadori, 2006. {{ISBN|978-88-04-56753-0}} (All about Totti) {{in lang|it}}\n*''La mia vita, i miei gol'' (book + DVD), Milano, Mondadori, 2007. {{ISBN|88-04-57241-8}} (My life, my goals) {{in lang|it}}\n*''Quando i bambini fanno \"ah\u00f3\" '' (book + DVD), Milano, Mondadori, 2009. {{ISBN|88-04-59004-1}} (When the children shout \"Ah\u00f